.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-CREATE 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-create \- Author a playbook directly from a prompt (no triage, no cache serve)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR create <prompt> [\-\-template <t>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
create force\-authors a fresh playbook from <prompt>, bypassing triage entirely —
unlike assist, it never serves a cache hit. It persists the result to the store
(and a cache entry) so a later assist for the same context can hit it.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\fR \fI<t>\fR
reserved (not yet implemented); parses but is a no\-op
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook create "set up a new Go module with golangci\-lint"
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
